Story of: “Sits Pretty “ 
Sits Pretty was a Kiowa woman with an alluring beauty and a wild spirit. She would often frequent the local club, looking to meet a man. Though she appeared to be charming and loving, she had a much darker agenda. Whenever she found a man to date, she would always end up taking all of his possessions and leaving him penniless and broken.

On one particular night, a man caught her eye. He was tall and handsome, and he seemed to be different than the rest. She slowly made her way over to him and they began to talk. As the night went on, they shared stories and laughed until the early hours of the morning.

Unknown to him, Sits Pretty had found a small cedar box he had placed on the table. As he was distracted, she grabbed it and quickly hid it away. Later that night, when she was alone, she opened the box and found a sage with cedar inside.

Without hesitation, Sits Pretty blew the sage and cedar into the wind. Immediately, her face was enveloped in a thick, black fog and she felt her body morph into that of a rabbit. 

She yelled and sobbed until the nearby tribal police arrived and realized that the trickster had struck again. There was no remedy for the affliction, and Sits Pretty was left with her new form. 

She was eventually taken to a nearby psychiatric hospital, where she has remained since. With each passing day, leaving her cursed as a rabbit for eternity…
